      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520024.0013.010-01.00.00%2520Gyproc%2520WR%252012.5%2520Saint-Gobain-EN_%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": "10.1",
          "title": "A1 - raw material supply",
          "description": "This module takes into account the extraction and processing of all raw materials (natural gypsum, recycled gypsum, additives, paper,…), energy and packaging which occur upstream to the manufacturing site."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": "10.2",
          "title": "A2 – transport to the manufacturer",
          "description": "This module includes the transportation of raw materials and packaging to the manufacturing site. The modelling includes road, boat and/or train transportations."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": "10.3",
          "title": "A3 - manufacturing",
          "description": "This module includes the manufacture of products and the manufacture of packaging. The production of packaging material is considered at this stage. The processing of any waste arising from this stage is also included."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": "10.4",
          "title": "A4 – transport to the building site",
          "description": "Plasterboards are categorized as 'loose products' in table 6 of the B-PCR. The following transport steps apply:\n– 40% directly to the construction site over 100 km with a 16-32 ton lorry\n– 60% to a supplier over 100 km with a 16 -32 ton lorry\n– 85% of these 60% is transported over 35 km from supplier to construction site with a 16-32 ton lorry\n– 15% of these 60% is transported over 35 km from supplier to construction site with a 7.5-16 ton lorry\n\nFuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport:\nTruck: >32 Ton - Diesel: 0.16l/km (default data ecoinvent)\nTruck: 16-32 Ton - Diesel: 0.03 l/km (default data ecoinvent)\nTruck: 7.5-16 Ton - Diesel: 0.4 l/km (default data ecoinvent)\n\nDistance (km): 60, 69.75, 5.25\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): Default data from ecoinvent\nBulk density of transported products: 824 kg/m3\nVolume capacity utilization factor: 1"
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": "10.5",
          "title": "A5 – installation in the building",
          "description": "At the construction site, packaging materials are released. Also 5% material losses have been taken into account\n\nProcesses necessary for the installation of the product:\n– Cutting the plasterboard to size (by hand),\n– Fixing the plasterboard on the framing with screws..\n– Filling the joint between plasterboards with jointing compound reinforced by jointing tape.\n\nFixation materials: 8 pcs Screws\nJointing materials: 0.33 kg Jointing compound, 1.23 m Jointing tape\nTreatments: -\nMaterial losses: 5% Plasterboard\nPackaging: 0.22 kg Wooden pallet\nAncillary materials for installation (specified by material): Insert information\nWater use: 0.105 litres\nOther resource use: none\nQuantitative description of energy type (regional mix) and consumption during the installation process: none\nWaste materials on the building site before waste processing, generated by the product's installation (specified by type): 0.515 (kg) scrap plasterboard\nOutput materials (specified by type) as result of waste processing at the building site e.g. of collection for recycling, for energy recovery, disposal (specified by route):\n– 5% of plasterboard : 20% recycling / 80% landfil\n– Wooden pallet: re-used 7 times\nDirect emissions to ambient air, soil and water: None\nDistance: 50 km to landfill, 30 km to recycling"
        },
        {
          "module": "B",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B – use stage (excluding potential savings)",
          "description": "Description of the stage:\nthe use stage is divided into the following modules:\n• B1: Use\n• B2: Maintenance\n• B3: Repair\n• B4: Replacement\n• B5: Refurbishment\n• B6: Operational energy use\n• B7: Operational water use\n\nDescription of the scenarios and additional technical information:\nThe product has a reference service life of 60 years. This assumes that the product will last in situ with no requirements for maintenance, repair, replacement, or refurbishment throughout this period. Therefore, it has no impact at this stage."
        },
        {
          "module": "C",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C: End of life",
          "description": "Description of the stage:\nthis stage includes the next modules:\n• C1: Deconstruction, demolition: The de-construction and/or dismantling of the product take part of the demolition of the entire building. In our case, a small amount of energy is considered 0.05 MJ/m².\n• C2: Transport to waste processing\nwe used standard eco invent data according B-EPD pcr\n• C3: Waste processing for reuse, recovery and/or recycling\n• C4: disposal, including provision and all transport, provision of all materials, products and related energy and water use\n\nModule C2 – Transport to waste processing\nType of vehicle: Truck 16-32 ton\nFuel consumption: Diesel 0.03 l/km (default data from ecoinvent)\nDistance: 50km (landfill), 30km (recycling), 100km (incineration)\nCapacity utilisation: Default data from ecoinvent\nDensity of products: 824 kg/m3\nAssumptions: Same truck for all the scenarios of end-of-life\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4\nWastes collected separately: 2.06 kg (20 % of plasterboard)\nWastes collected as mixed construction waste: 0\nWaste for re-use: none\nWaste for recycling: 1.99 kg (20% of gypsum)\nWaste for energy recovery: 0.07 kg (20% of paperliner)\nWaste for final disposal: 8.58 kg (80% of plasterboard and 100% of auxiliaries (eg: jointing compounds, tape))"
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": "10.8",
          "title": "D – Benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries",
          "description": "In the module D is declared the environmental benefits from reusable products, recyclable materials, or energy recovery. Module D considers product raw materials, and relevant packaging valorisation in recycling and/or in incineration with energy recovery.\n\nQuantitative description of the loads beyond the system boundaries:\nThe processing of recycled materials, such as gypsum and paper liner\n\nQuantitative description of the benefits beyond the system boundaries:\nThe recycled material from the gypsum and the energy recovery from incineration of paper"
        }
      ]
